    "body": "<p><b>Original Confluence URL:</b> <a href=\"https://qbdocs.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/IAM/pages/1062469984\">https://qbdocs.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/IAM/pages/1062469984</a> - please cross-check the quality of the ZD article with the Confluence counterpart and remove this line before publishing the ZD article</p>\n\n<h2>Table of Contents</h2>\n<ul class=\"toc\">\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#header-1\">SSO - Single Sign On:</a></li>\n</ul>\n</ul><h1 id=\"header-1\"><strong>SSO - Single Sign On:</strong></h1><p>A user has to login once in one context (browser, smartphone, operating system). If the user is authenticated in one app the user is also authenticated in another app in that context.</p><p>Example: I log-in to GMail in Mozilla, I navigate to Google Docs â†’ I am already logged in at Google Docs</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:src=\"https://qbdocs.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/996507859/Glossary%20-%20Part%201%20-%20SSO(1).png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1568278125965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1041\"><ri:url ri:value=\"https://qbdocs.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/996507859/Glossary%20-%20Part%201%20-%20SSO(1).png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1568278125965&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1041\"></ri:url></ac:image><p><br></p>",
